title: One day I met something special.
subTitle: It is my little secret.
mainBody:
Don’t include photos, screenshots, or interface elements. 

 Photographic details can be very hard to see at small sizes. Screenshots are too complex for an app icon and don’t generally help communicate your app’s purpose. Interface elements in an icon are misleading and confusing.

subTitle: But “my parents” don’t want to understand me :c
park: Lake Clark National Park and Preserve
mainBody:
Use words only when they’re essential or part of a logo. 

 An app’s name appears below its icon on the Home screen. Don’t include nonessential words that repeat the name or tell people what to do with your app, like Watch or Play. If your design includes any text, emphasize words that relate to the actual content your app offers.

title: Helll, was you happy?
park: Klondike Gold Rush National Historical Park
mainBody: Design a recognizable icon. People shouldn’t have to analyze the icon to figure out what it represents. For example, the Mail app icon uses an envelope, which is universally associated with mail. Take time to design a beautiful and engaging abstract icon that artistically represents your app’s purpose.
